<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5390.1.1>
    dc:creator "Bertani, Rogério" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Taxonomic revision and cladistic analysis of Lasiodora C. L. Koch, 1850 (Araneae, Theraphosidae) with notes on related genera" ;
    bibo:endPage "116" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-12-27" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "5390" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434522>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434524>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434526>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434648>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434650>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434652>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434654>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434660> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434522>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–15. Stridulatory setae of prolateral coxa I, males. 8, L. parahybana, Brazil, state of Pernambuco, Cabo de Santo Agostinho. 9, L. sertaneja n. sp. (IBSP 4127B). 10, L. camurujipe n. sp. (MNRJ 7764). 11, L. franciscana n. sp. (IBSP 8050). 12, L. subcanens (IBSP 9546). 13, L. klugi (MNRJ 7742). 14, L. benedeni (IBSP 84328). 15, L. klugi, Brazil, state of Bahia, Ilhéus. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434522/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434524>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Strict consensus of three cladograms obtained with setk.run and concavity 7.8125. All characters non-additive. Fit = 7.38251, length = 161.30. Absolute/relative Bremer support are in each node. The names of the genera and species in the cladogram are in accordance with the results obtained in the cladistic analysis carried out here, and do not consider the new genera and transfers proposed by Galleti-Lima et al. 2023." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434524/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434526>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Map of Brazil and its relief, showing geographic records of L. benedeni (yellow square), L. camurujipe n. sp. (inverted orange triangle), L. franciscana n. sp. (blue dot), L. klugi (red dot), L. parahybana (light blue triangle), L. sertaneja n. sp. (pink star), and L. subcanens (purple hexagon). “?” represents questionable records." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434526/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434648>
    dc:description "FIGURES 225─230. Lasiodora sertaneja n. sp. (225─229) male holotype (IBSP 343484). (225─227) left palp bulb. 225, retrolateral. 226, prolateral. 227, dorsal. (228─229) left tibial apophysis. 228, ventral. 229, prolateral. 230, female paratype (IBSP 343485), spermathecae, dorsal. Scale bar = 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434648/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434650>
    dc:description "FIGURES 231─235. Lasiodora sertaneja n. sp., male holotype (IBSP 343484), stridulatory apparatus. (231─232) left maxilla, retrolateral. 231, general view. 232, detail of spiniform setae on upper and lower areas. (233─235) left coxa I, prolateral. 233, general view. 234, detail of stridulatory setae. 235, detail of area below suture. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434650/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434652>
    dc:description "FIGURES 236─240. Lasiodora sertaneja n. sp., female paratype (IBSP 343485), stridulatory apparatus. (236─237) left maxilla, retrolateral. 236, general view. 237, detail of spiniform setae on upper and lower areas. (238─240) left coxa I, prolateral. 238, general view. 239, detail of stridulatory setae. 240, detail of area below suture. Scale bar = 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434652/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434654>
    dc:description "FIGURES 241─244. Lasiodora sertaneja n. sp., stridulatory apparatus, variation. (241─242) male (IBSP 4377). 241, left maxilla, retrolateral. 242, left coxa I, prolateral. (243─244) male (IBSP 8763). 243, left maxilla, retrolateral. 244, left coxa I, prolateral. Scale bar = 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434660>
    dc:description "FIGURES 253─254. Maps showing records of Lasiodora sertaneja n. sp. in northeastern and southeastern Brazil. 253, relief. 254, biomes. Forested areas of Fig. 254 are in green shades, on east (Brazilian Atlantic Forest) and on west (Amazon). Brown areas are of Cerrado; and pinkish, Caatinga. There is a questionable record, not represented in the map, for the state of Pará, Brazil." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434660/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

